## Architecture Rules

### Design Patterns (Required)
- {{e.g., Use `typing.Protocol` for interfaces, not ABC}}
- {{e.g., Use `@dataclass(frozen=True)` for immutable data}}
- {{e.g., Use factory methods (`from_settings()`) for complex initialization}}
- {{e.g., Dependency injection via constructor parameters}}

### Design Patterns (Prohibited)
- {{e.g., No deep inheritance hierarchies (max depth: 1)}}
- {{e.g., No global mutable state}}
- {{e.g., No synchronous blocking calls in async code}}

## Code Standards

### Naming Conventions
- {{e.g., snake_case for functions and variables}}
- {{e.g., PascalCase for classes}}
- {{e.g., SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE for constants}}

### Documentation
- {{e.g., Google-style docstrings}}
- {{e.g., Type annotations on all public functions}}
- {{e.g., Module docstrings required}}

## Security Requirements
- {{e.g., No secrets in code or logs}}
- {{e.g., Input validation at API boundaries}}
- {{e.g., Use environment variables for configuration}}

## Definition of Done

A task is complete when:
- [ ] All acceptance criteria pass
- [ ] Linter passes (`ruff check .`)
- [ ] Type checker passes (`ty check src`)
- [ ] Tests pass (`pytest`)
- [ ] No new security vulnerabilities
- [ ] Code follows all architecture rules above

